  "paper_analysis": {
    "summary": "This paper reports a multimodal host–guest complexation strategy for FAPbI3-based perovskite solar cells using the crown ether dibenzo-21-crown-7 (DB21C7) to deliver Cs+ ions in chlorobenzene without damaging the film. The treatment creates a Cs-rich surface and a Cs gradient into the bulk, passivates Pb-related defects, suppresses non-radiative recombination, improves phase stability, and yields devices with >24% PCE and strong operational stability.",
